## Part 4: Docker

### Dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim
# Official Python image. slim = minimal size.

WORKDIR /app
# All commands run from /app. Created automatically.

COPY requirements.txt .
# Copy requirements FIRST — layer caching optimization.

RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
# Only rebuilds when requirements.txt changes.

COPY . .
# Copy app code last. Code changes don't bust pip cache.

EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

### Layer caching — why order matters
WRONG:                          RIGHT:
COPY . .                        COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install                 RUN pip install
→ any code change               COPY . .
  re-downloads everything       → pip only re-runs when
                                  requirements.txt changes

### .dockerignore
venv/
__pycache__/
.git/
.env
*.log

### Key commands
docker build -t my-app:latest .           build image
docker run -p 5000:5000 my-app:latest    run (host:container port)
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 my-app        run in background
docker ps                                 list running containers
docker stop container-name               stop container
docker images                            list all images
docker logs container-name              see output

### Running in minikube
